An Act relative to the appointment of the police chief in the city of Fall River.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Notwithstanding the provisions of any general or special law to the
2 contrary, the position of Police Chief in the City of Fall River shall, upon the effective date of
3 this Act, be subject to the provisions of Chapter 31 of the Massachusetts General Laws and all
4 rules and regulations promulgated thereunder governing civil service.
5 SECTION 2. The Mayor of the City of Fall River shall remain the appointing authority
6 for the Police Chief and the terms and conditions of the Police Chief's employment contract shall
7 be subject to Section 1080 of General Laws Chapter 41, for a period not to exceed three (3)
8 years.
9 SECTION 3. The Police Chief shall be the head of the Fall River Police Department,
10 shall be responsible for the management and operation of said police department, and shall be the
11 "Appointing Authority" for all employees of the police department in accordance with Section of
1 of 2

12 General Laws Chapter 31, with all the rights, duties and privileges appurtenant thereto and as
13 contained in subsequent sections of Chapter 31 and any other general or special law applicable to
14 chiefs of departments.
15 SECTION 4. This Act shall apply to any vacancy in the position of Police Chief
16 occurring on or after the effective date of this Act. Nothing in this Act shall affect the civil
17 service status, seniority, or rights of any person employed in the Fall River Police Department as
18 of the effective date of this Act.
19 SECTION 5. This Act shall take effect upon its passage.
